column7: Possibly named after Cecilia Catharina Lange, the Danish wife of Sultan Abu Bakar (Zubaidah binti Abdullah)

"The word "selegie" is believed to be a Malay word that refers to a wooden spear sharpened and hardened by fire. A Bugis pirate race known as Orang Selegie were said to have lived on a hill known as Mount Sophia, located near Selegie Road during Singapore's early years." - Infopedia

Named after Edwy Lyonet Talma, a member of the Malayan Civil Service originally from Barbados and a leader in the Eurasian community. http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/infopedia/articles/SIP_409_2005-01-25.html
Derives its name from the large Cantonese burial ground known as Peck San Theng (碧山亭, bi4shan1ting2)
Possibly named after the Battle of Aliwal, part of the Anglo-Sikh war
